🔹 🔥 Final Interview Answer

“If an EC2 instance restarted automatically, I would first check AWS scheduled events to see if it was due to maintenance or hardware issues. 
Then I would verify whether the instance was replaced by an auto scaling group. 
If not, I would check system logs for OS-level issues like kernel panic or resource exhaustion. 
I would also review CloudWatch metrics to understand if there was a spike in CPU, memory, or disk usage before the restart.”

